{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"compacted_at":1783658154039283002,"compiled_state":{"alias":"breaded-ammonitic-elephant","assignee":"","author":"RebarBotNava","bridge_alerts":[],"claim_harness":"claude-code_2-1-206_agent","claim_remote_session":null,"claimed_session":"ae74bad7-1aaa-45ff-83d3-da8013db8211","comments":[{"author":"RebarBotNava","body":"FORCE_CLAIM: plan-review gate bypassed by user approval — no plan-review attestation was verified. Reason: \"User-authorized (v1.0 epic session): background plan-review stalled without signing the epic; force-claiming to unblock OSS front-door implementation.\".","timestamp":1783647554303422001},{"author":"RebarBotNava","body":"EPIC CONSISTENCY AUDIT (re-read CONTRIBUTING/CLAUDE/SUPPORT/README + all new docs — GOVERNANCE/MAINTAINERS/CODE_OF_CONDUCT, your-first-change, review-policy, releasing, release-notes, dco-rollout-evidence, ADR 0037/0038, issue templates, dependabot.yml, lockdown.yml, cliff.toml, CHANGELOG — as one set).\n\nPASS (7/8 invariants):\n1. Vote-semantics SINGLE-SOURCE: the coverage-gap sub-reason enumeration (gate-disabled/llm-unavailable/scanner/review-error/indeterminate/merge-review) is a contributor-facing table ONLY in docs/review-policy.md; CONTRIBUTING §2c is the slimmed summary+pointer; README + tutorial don't duplicate it. (docs/adr/0015 mentions the tags as an internal historical record — allowed.)\n2. PR posture (read-only mirror, PRs redirect to Gerrit via lockdown bot) consistent across README/CONTRIBUTING/SUPPORT/GOVERNANCE/ADR-0037/lockdown.yml/dependabot.yml/issue templates.\n3. Issues ENABLED as primary channel; Discussions OFF — consistent.\n4. DCO consistent (git commit -s / developercertificate.org / DCO-not-CLA) across CONTRIBUTING/tutorial/CLAUDE.\n5. CoC contact identical (hello@navapbc.com, role-based) in SUPPORT + CODE_OF_CONDUCT, matches GOVERNANCE §6.\n6. Gerrit URL consistent everywhere.\n7. Outsider push uses 'git push origin HEAD:refs/for/main' with no Nava-internal refs.\n\nFIXED (1 real contradiction): CONTRIBUTING §5 claimed Dependabot version-update PRs were 'intentionally NOT configured', contradicting the dependabot.yml that chihuahua shipped + releasing.md + ADR-0037. Remediated in change 472 (§5 now describes the github-actions advisory-PR posture + no-pip-ecosystem rationale). \nFALSE POSITIVE (no action): an audit finding claimed SUPPORT.md references a non-existent PR template; .github/pull_request_template.md does exist (canary links it) — SUPPORT.md is correct.\n\nAlso: 0 dangling relative links across all new/edited docs. Audit COMPLETE; the one contradiction is remediated.","timestamp":1783658154039283001}],"created_at":1783628660727667001,"deps":[{"link_uuid":"53e0b1ad-40b4-4937-b4bf-6701a8139d61","relation":"relates_to","target_id":"5163-8b5e-064f-40e1"}],"description":"# OSS v1.0.0 community front door — contribution intake, governance, and release artifacts\n\n## Context\n\nrebar is technically near-1.0 (PyPI Trusted Publishing + PEP 740 attestations, immutable releases, `docs/api-stability.md` stability matrix, event-schema forward-compat) but the public contribution funnel is closed: GitHub (navapbc/rebar) is a read-only mirror with Issues and Discussions disabled (verified via API 2026-07-09: `has_issues: false`), and while CONTRIBUTING.md already documents an external Gerrit path (§1–§3), there is no GitHub-side intake, no governance/DCO/review-policy artifacts, and no user-facing changelog. Three converging assessments (internal repo audit; an external deep-research report; peer research across Go, Chromium, Qt, LibreOffice, Wikimedia, OpenStack, Eclipse) identify public intake + written governance as the only blockers to a credible v1.0.0.\n\nPeer convergence establishes the design: KEEP Gerrit — Wikimedia reversed its GitLab migration in June 2024 over the review model (https://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/GitLab/Migration_status), JGit/EGit migrated TO GerritHub rather than accept PRs (https://gitenterprise.me/2023/11/21/14-years-of-jgit-egit-code-reviews-migrated-to-gerrithub/) — and pair the wall with a ramp: bot-answered PRs (LibreOffice/Wikimedia pattern), a first-change tutorial, a shepherded-patch fallback, GitHub Issues as zero-friction intake (Go's model), DCO enforced at the Gerrit server (OpenStack TC resolution 2025-05-20, https://governance.openstack.org/tc/resolutions/20250520-replace-the-cla-with-dco-for-all-contributions.html), and skipped non-convergent ceremony (CODEOWNERS, GPG-signed tags, RC trains — each a recorded non-goal with rationale in a child).\n\nStars/forks/contributor counts are explicitly OUT of scope; success is artifact completeness and funnel quality.\n\nCross-child protocols (binding on all children):\n- **Vote-semantics single source:** `docs/review-policy.md` (child wrathful-preregal-blobfish) is the sole authoritative DOCUMENT for Gerrit vote semantics; its table's content is transcribed from the code enums (`_TAG_SUFFIXES` in adapter.py + the merge-path tags in voter.py) — document-of-record and source-of-truth are distinct and both are named. Every other doc links to it rather than duplicating the table. Until it lands, CONTRIBUTING.md §2c remains the interim authority.\n- **Ownership inversion for cross-links:** a child that CREATES a doc never forward-links to a sibling's not-yet-existing doc; the sibling that creates the later doc owns adding links into earlier docs. Dependency edges: PR-posture and review-policy each depend_on the onboarding tutorial (their artifacts link it).\n- **Decisions live in the repo**, not only on tickets: design decisions are recorded as ADRs under `docs/adr/` or in the owning doc (e.g. `docs/releasing.md`), with a ticket comment pointing at the artifact.\n- **Shepherded-patch DCO interplay:** a shepherded contribution needs the ORIGINAL author's `Signed-off-by` (contributor runs `git commit -s` before `git format-patch`) plus the shepherd's own sign-off added on amend — the OpenStack two-trailer convention; documented in both the DCO and PR-posture children.\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n- GitHub intake works and is self-explanatory: Issues enabled with structured forms; an issue can be filed with no Gerrit account, no local checkout, and no knowledge beyond the form itself (verifiable from the rendered chooser, not a timing claim).\n- The path from GitHub to a merged Gerrit change is documented end-to-end in one tutorial an outsider can follow with zero Nava-internal knowledge (measured by concrete checks in the onboarding child, e.g. no references to internal-only groups/layouts on the happy path).\n- A no-Gerrit patch fallback is published. Authorship preservation via `git am` is promised only if experiment E2 confirms Gerrit's Forge Author permission is (or can be) granted; if E2 fails, the documented fallback is `Co-authored-by:` credit and the policy text says so (go/no-go, not an unconditional promise).\n- Governance, review policy, DCO, and maintainer info are published, each grounded in a named peer convention (curl/CNCF, Chromium-CQ/Zuul, OpenStack/moby — URLs in the children).\n- Release artifacts (CHANGELOG, dependabot, README front door, 1.0 declaration mechanics) match documented 2026 Python-tool convergence.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] All nine child stories closed: GitHub intake; PR posture; onboarding tutorial + CONTRIBUTING; README front door; DCO; governance docs; review policy; CHANGELOG; release hygiene / 1.0 declaration.\n- [ ] The four pre-flight experiments (E1 fork-side UX with has_pull_requests=false; E2 Gerrit Forge Author ACL; E3 PR-event dependency audit; E4 rebar-ticket trailer policy for shepherded patches) are executed AND each dependent child's design is updated or explicitly confirmed against the outcome (outcome-framed: an experiment that invalidates an assumption must change the affected child before that child is worked). E3-discovered breakage is fixed (or ticketed via discovered_from) by the PR-posture child.\n- [ ] The `docs/api-stability.md` pre-1.0 caveat flip and the Development Status classifier bump are staged for the v1.0.0 release change (release-hygiene child names the landing vehicle).\n- [ ] Final consistency audit (epic-level, before epic close, owned by the epic executor): re-read CONTRIBUTING.md, CLAUDE.md, SUPPORT.md, README.md, and all new docs as one set; verify no artifact contradicts the Gerrit-primary workflow or another artifact (including the vote-semantics single-source rule); record the audit result as an epic comment.\n- [ ] Cross-link completeness: `docs/release-notes.md` carries a pointer to CHANGELOG.md (owned by the changelog child); every new doc is reachable from CONTRIBUTING.md or README.md.","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[{"path":"README.md","reason":"front-door pass (via children)"},{"path":"CONTRIBUTING.md","reason":"external-path restructure (via children)"},{"path":"docs/your-first-change.md","reason":"new onboarding tutorial (via children)"},{"path":".github/","reason":"issue forms, lockdown workflow, dependabot (via children)"},{"path":"GOVERNANCE.md","reason":"new governance doc (via children)"}],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[["relates_to","5163-8b5e-064f-40e1"]],"parent_id":null,"parent_status_uuid":"0608dbe2-7dc8-4b63-8a44-0f771df5ed4b","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":2,"reverts":[],"signature":null,"status":"in_progress","tags":[],"ticket_id":"fc2a-9fa5-def6-4e68","ticket_type":"epic","title":"OSS v1.0.0 community front door — contribution intake, governance, and release artifacts","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["406ac368-cf60-4741-8eca-98c9d33ec1f9","20725dbe-9a20-4545-ae93-fcdf0b8ca72c","ca7078f1-29ae-4038-9dc0-c41669903106","53e0b1ad-40b4-4937-b4bf-6701a8139d61","73befeaf-b764-44db-a426-50d52f7cb996","826c7e3f-f901-456b-8130-0bb0517ad527","0608dbe2-7dc8-4b63-8a44-0f771df5ed4b","2de14fb0-fdba-47e7-8715-bd2bbe817de2","5172c772-6975-4a6e-b032-f18e887cb9d3","f9315e24-939d-4008-945b-8fc5d423f441"]},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"SNAPSHOT","timestamp":1783658154039283002,"uuid":"4669a3b4-f8fd-448e-8e92-0967fe032987"}